WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:12.378 --> 00:13.743
Yo, you need help
lighting that?

00:16.481 --> 00:18.047
All right. Where's your damn wallet?

00:18.049 --> 00:19.348
Come on, man!
Get it out!

00:19.350 --> 00:20.917
I'm getting it.
I'll cut you, man. I swear.

00:20.919 --> 00:22.585
Take it easy. I'm getting it.

00:22.587 --> 00:24.921
All units move in,
move in, move in!

00:33.164 --> 00:35.131
I'm a cop!

00:35.133 --> 00:37.934
Get off me! I'm a cop!
I'm a cop! Don't fight me, man!

00:37.936 --> 00:39.535
Don't fight me!

00:39.537 --> 00:40.702
Jamie!

00:45.009 --> 00:46.009
Stay right there!

00:46.577 --> 00:47.543
Hands up!

00:47.545 --> 00:48.644
Jamie, are you okay?

00:48.646 --> 00:49.812
Yeah, I think so.

00:49.814 --> 00:51.847
What'd you do that for?
I dropped the knife!

00:51.849 --> 00:53.749
Doesn't matter. You grabbed
for my gun. You're under arrest.

00:53.751 --> 00:54.850
No, I didn't!

00:54.852 --> 00:57.385
You have the right
to remain silent.

00:57.387 --> 01:01.523
I know. My dad's a cop.

01:07.064 --> 01:09.164
<i>Michael,</i>

01:09.166 --> 01:11.032
you up? Breakfast is done!

01:11.034 --> 01:12.467
You know I don't eat breakfast.

01:12.469 --> 01:14.436
Uh, you should
the day of tryouts

01:14.438 --> 01:16.804
for a big math
competition.

01:16.806 --> 01:18.039
You ready?

01:18.041 --> 01:19.040
Yep.

01:19.042 --> 01:20.808
Do you have your calculator?

01:20.810 --> 01:23.374
I told you, we're not allowed
to bring calculators.

01:23.398 --> 01:24.279
Baby,

01:24.280 --> 01:26.280
can you help me
with this bow tie?

01:26.282 --> 01:28.115
That's what you're wearing to
the opening of a youth facility?

01:28.117 --> 01:29.249
I'm not wearing it
for the youth.

01:29.251 --> 01:30.217
I'm wearing it for the cameras.

01:30.219 --> 01:31.151
It's corny.

01:31.153 --> 01:32.553
Say what?
It makes you look

01:32.555 --> 01:33.921
like you work in a restaurant.

01:33.923 --> 01:35.122
Oh, so now you're
a fashion critic?

01:35.124 --> 01:36.824
- Just saying.
- Now you're gonna get it.

01:36.826 --> 01:37.959
Come on, slugger. Come on.

01:37.961 --> 01:39.026
Huh?

01:40.929 --> 01:42.229
Good luck today, son.

01:42.231 --> 01:44.398
And be careful out there, hmm?
Dad,

01:44.400 --> 01:45.699
I'm going to a math contest.

01:45.701 --> 01:47.834
I'm saying,
if you run into the police...

01:47.836 --> 01:50.770
Be polite but know your rights.
All right.

01:50.772 --> 01:53.140
Get out of here.

01:53.142 --> 01:56.143
Rumble, young
man. Rumble.

02:06.488 --> 02:07.438
Mommy, please,
where are you?

02:07.462 --> 02:09.323
Will you shut up?!

02:09.324 --> 02:12.659
Mommy. Mommy.
Well, here we go again.

02:12.661 --> 02:15.194
Oh, my God. At least
she's not singing

02:15.196 --> 02:16.962
“99 Bottles of Beer” anymore.
Mommy, please don't

02:16.964 --> 02:18.831
let them hit me again.

02:18.833 --> 02:20.506
Mommy, don't let them
hit me again.

02:20.530 --> 02:21.268
Yo,

02:21.269 --> 02:23.903
Rent-a-cop, we may... we
might need to pull over again.

02:23.905 --> 02:25.771
Please, Mommy.
Mommy, it hurts. It hurts.

02:25.773 --> 02:27.640
Please,
Mommy,

02:27.642 --> 02:28.841
it hurts. Please.

02:28.843 --> 02:31.343
Please, Mommy,
don't let them hit me again.

02:31.345 --> 02:33.178
Hey, guys. For real now.

02:33.180 --> 02:34.813
Mommy, please!

02:34.815 --> 02:37.082
Yo, seriously!
She's not faking now!

02:37.084 --> 02:39.384
Hey, you want to go back there
and tell 'em to shut up again?

02:39.386 --> 02:42.120
No. You shut 'em up.

02:42.122 --> 02:43.889
Buckle up.

02:43.891 --> 02:45.624
Guys, don't do this!

02:58.972 --> 03:01.440
This lady's out! Stop!

03:01.442 --> 03:03.808
Stop the van, man! Stop!

03:12.418 --> 03:16.287
Yo, how did everybody do
on the game theory question?

03:16.289 --> 03:18.422
- Beasted on it.
- Well, what do you expect?

03:18.424 --> 03:20.524
His mom's a teacher,
and his dad's a sponsor.

03:20.526 --> 03:21.892
Nobody gave me the answers.

03:21.894 --> 03:23.961
Whatever.
Hey, who's up

03:23.963 --> 03:26.830
for chilling at my mom's with
some <i>Call to War 2</i> on the Xbox?

03:26.832 --> 03:28.765
So lame. <i>3's</i>
about to come out.

03:28.767 --> 03:30.720
Hey, guys,
I'll catch up to you later!

03:30.744 --> 03:31.436
What's up?

03:31.437 --> 03:32.733
Just got to take care
of something!

03:32.757 --> 03:34.306
All right. Later, G.

03:34.307 --> 03:36.840
Really, Anthony? You're
pulling me out of a meeting?

03:36.842 --> 03:39.542
Come down to the scene
of a traffic accident?

03:39.544 --> 03:41.211
You need to see
what happened here.

03:41.213 --> 03:44.514
Looks like more of a job
for Highway Patrol.

03:44.516 --> 03:46.817
Yeah, well, this is the private
prison van that was supposed

03:46.819 --> 03:49.753
to be bringing up the witness
for our big fraud trial.

03:49.755 --> 03:51.354
You mean the one that was
in custody in Florida,

03:51.356 --> 03:53.456
Kenny Becker?
Yeah, Kenny was in the van

03:53.458 --> 03:56.192
when it got T-boned
going through the intersection.

03:56.194 --> 03:58.528
It was carrying a bunch of other
prisoners getting picked up

03:58.530 --> 04:01.197
and dropped off all along
the Eastern Seaboard.

04:01.199 --> 04:02.465
So where's Kenny?

04:02.467 --> 04:05.101
We're sorting through
all the IDs,

04:05.103 --> 04:06.269
trying
to figure it out.

04:06.271 --> 04:09.939
Got at least four injured,
one escaped.

04:12.476 --> 04:13.542
And throw in

04:13.544 --> 04:14.744
one D.O.A.

04:14.746 --> 04:16.278
So our witness is in the wind

04:16.279 --> 04:18.113
and we have no way
of tracking him?

04:18.116 --> 04:22.084
That's how it goes
when you travel economy.

04:26.524 --> 04:28.457
Why am I not getting
any information?!

04:28.459 --> 04:31.893
I have a right to
know! I have a right!

04:31.895 --> 04:34.095
You show me! Tell me
who is in charge here!

04:34.097 --> 04:35.864
- Is that Potter?
- That's him.

04:35.866 --> 04:37.999
The hell is he doing?
Take it easy.

04:38.001 --> 04:40.264
- Take it easy?
- What is going on here?!

04:40.265 --> 04:41.678
Our job's not hard
enough without this guy

04:41.679 --> 04:44.946
screwing up our crime scene and
making our life more difficult?

04:44.948 --> 04:47.982
The victim's his son,
Michael Potter. 15 years old.

04:47.984 --> 04:50.152
Three shots
at close range.

04:50.154 --> 04:52.720
That is my son!

04:52.722 --> 04:55.271
Oh, my God.
Somebody, you tell me, you tell me!

04:55.295 --> 04:56.052
What do we know?

04:56.053 --> 04:58.486
No witnesses to the attack.
Looks like he was taking

04:58.488 --> 05:00.788
a shortcut through this lot
to get home.

05:00.790 --> 05:03.124
The boy was an honor student at
Crispus Attucks High School.

05:03.126 --> 05:04.159
Supposed
to be

05:04.161 --> 05:05.960
on his way home
from a math contest.

05:05.962 --> 05:07.662
Was it a robbery? What?

05:07.664 --> 05:09.264
His cell phone was still
in his backpack.

05:09.266 --> 05:10.798
Cash was still
in his wallet.

05:10.800 --> 05:13.834
Maybe he resisted?
But three shots

05:13.836 --> 05:15.402
is a lot
for a robbery.

05:15.404 --> 05:18.005
Talk to me!

05:19.909 --> 05:21.709
Is it true?

05:21.711 --> 05:25.512
Is it true? Is it true?

05:25.514 --> 05:26.681
No, is it true?

05:26.683 --> 05:28.449
No!

05:29.819 --> 05:30.818
Let go of me.

05:30.820 --> 05:32.352
Let go of me. No.
Baby, calm down!

05:32.354 --> 05:35.789
No, I need to see him! No!

05:35.791 --> 05:38.459
My son!

05:38.461 --> 05:40.427
I have to see
my son! No!

05:40.429 --> 05:42.696
That's my boy, Reagan!

05:42.698 --> 05:45.132
That's my boy in that dirt
right there!

05:45.134 --> 05:49.069
Reagan, you better do this
right! That's my son!

05:54.186 --> 05:58.186
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ Blue Bloods 7x10 ♪</font></b>
<font color="#00FFFF">Unbearable Loss</font>
